name: Kayaking excursion in the Oslo Fjord
shortDescription: The Oslo fjord is a popular tourist destination and many take ferries to the islands. Join Mad Goats on a guided kayak excursion around Høvedøya!
description:
The Oslo fjord is a popular tourist destination and many take ferries to the islands. Are you one of those who want a bit more of an adventure? If yes, then you can join Mad Goats on a guided kayak excursion around the main island: Høvedøya!

During the summer months, the water temperature rises over 20° C, that's perfect for those who may be tempted to swim while you take a break on the island. If you would rather have solid ground under your feet, you can explore the island, eat or sunbathe. The outing lasts approximately 3 hours.

Are you afraid that you do not have enough experience paddling a kayak? Don't worry, no experience is required, this trip is suitable for anyone. You just need to have wanted to have an outdoor adventure! You can choose either to paddle your own kayak or a double sea kayak, which is more stable.

The Oslo fjord is a sheltered area and the sea is usually calm, but since the weather is unpredictable the trip can sometimes be a little bit more exciting than usual. Therefore, you'll have an instructor who not only has unsurpassed skills in a kayak but also the common sense to determine when the conditions are too dangerous for beginners to paddle.

name: Island Hopping in the Oslo Fjord
shortDescription: Discover the world-renowned Oslo Fjord with its numerous islands like a local!
description:
Discover the world-renowned Oslo Fjord with its numerous islands like a local!

The Oslo Fjord is the perfect way to freshen up during summer close to the lovely Norwegian capital. The Fjord, which is one of the nine venues of the Class 1 World Powerboat Championship, has a multitude of islands, each with its own identity and history. The island of Hovedøya has monastery ruins, Gressholmen is famous for hosting rabbits. Lindøya is known for their cozy cabins at the water’s edge.

One can't think of a better way to experience everything the Fjord has to offer than by this island hopping tour, during which you will explore 1000-year-old ruins, a gorgeous hidden beach, and unique traditional wooden cabins.

Add to that swimming in the warm water of the Fjord and hiking through the forests and sea cliffs! You've got yourself the perfect island hopping combination!

Wait no more and book your summer island hopping tour of the Oslo Fjord now!
